{
  "texts": [
    "The distribution of convergence times deviates significantly from geometric patterns, a finding that aligns with the observations of Kalimeris et al. [82].",
    "Their study highlights that models trained with SGD exhibit a tendency to increase in complexity throughout the training process. 2.",
    "Deep models trained with SGD demonstrate an ability to master the sparse parity task in a number of iterations approaching asymptotic optimality, a phenomenon challenging to clarify without introducing an explicit sparsity prior.",
    "However, it's noteworthy that the inherent sparsity bias may stem from the deep model architecture itself.",
    "Mingard et al. [83] provide insights into this aspect, demonstrating that such models exhibit a bias toward simpler functions."
  ]
}